    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the<strong> chips</strong> to a baking tray with your <strong>nigella seeds</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-nuggets-sweet-potato-chips-and-masala-saag-beans/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>lime[s]</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-nuggets-sweet-potato-chips-and-masala-saag-beans/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-nuggets-sweet-potato-chips-and-masala-saag-beans/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>paneer</strong> into bite-sized cubes</p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> in a bowl with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>garam masala </strong>and<strong> half </strong>your <strong>curry powder </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and mix it all together</p><p>Add the <strong>cubed paneer</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up until the paneer is fully coated</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-nuggets-sweet-potato-chips-and-masala-saag-beans/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ginger paste</strong>, <strong>remaining garam masala</strong>, <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, the juice of half the <strong>lime[s]</strong> and your <strong>baked beans </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min further or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-nuggets-sweet-potato-chips-and-masala-saag-beans/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated paneer</strong> and cook for 5-6 min until golden, turning occasionally for even colouring</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>golden paneer</strong> to a plate \u2013 these are your <strong>spiced paneer nuggets</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-nuggets-sweet-potato-chips-and-masala-saag-beans/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the beans have thickened, add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min further or until starting to wilt \u2013 these are your <strong>masala saag beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/paneer-nuggets-sweet-potato-chips-and-masala-saag-beans/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spiced paneer nuggets</strong> with the <strong>chips </strong>and <strong>masala saag beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
